KW  - Institutional investors
KW  - Competition for flow
KW  - Governance via exit
KW  - Correlated trading
AB  - The growth of the asset management industry has made it commonplace for firms to have multiple institutional blockholders. In such firms, the strength of governance via exit depends on how blockholders react to each other’s exit. We present a model to show that open-ended institutional investors such as mutual funds react strongly to an informed blockholder’s exit, leading to correlated exits that enhance corporate governance. Our analysis points to a new role for mutual funds in corporate governance. We examine the trades of mutual funds around exits by activist hedge funds to present empirical evidence consistent with our model.
